.TH "SQUEEZE" "1" "2026\-04\-11" "Winix" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
squeeze \- compress and decompress files
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]squeeze\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[I]file\f[R]\&...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Compress and decompress files using gzip, brotli, or zstd.
Supports pipe mode (stdin/stdout), multi\-file batch processing, and
gzip\-compatible flags.
.PP
With no files, reads from stdin and writes to stdout (pipe mode).
Output format defaults to gzip unless \f[B]\(enbrotli\f[R] or
\f[B]\(enzstd\f[R] is given.
.PP
Decompression (\f[B]\-d\f[R]) auto\-detects the format from magic bytes
\(em the file extension is not required.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-d\f[R], \f[B]\(endecompress\f[R]
Decompress (auto\-detects format from magic bytes).
.TP
\f[B]\-b\f[R], \f[B]\(enbrotli\f[R]
Use brotli format.
.TP
\f[B]\-z\f[R], \f[B]\(enzstd\f[R]
Use zstd format.
.TP
\f[B]\(enlevel\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R]
Compression level (see COMPRESSION LEVELS).
.TP
\f[B]\-1\f[R] .. \f[B]\-9\f[R]
Shortcut for \f[B]\(enlevel 1\f[R] ..
\f[B]\(enlevel 9\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\-c\f[R], \f[B]\(enstdout\f[R]
Write to stdout instead of creating an output file.
.TP
\f[B]\-o\f[R], \f[B]\(enoutput\f[R] \f[I]FILE\f[R]
Explicit output file (single input only; \f[B]\-\f[R] for stdout).
.TP
\f[B]\-f\f[R], \f[B]\(enforce\f[R]
Overwrite existing output files.
.TP
\f[B]\(enremove\f[R]
Delete the input file after a successful operation.
.TP
\f[B]\-k\f[R], \f[B]\(enkeep\f[R]
Keep the original file (default; accepted for gzip compatibility).
.TP
\f[B]\-v\f[R], \f[B]\(enverbose\f[R]
Show stats even when piped.
.TP
\f[B]\-q\f[R], \f[B]\(enquiet\f[R]
Suppress stats even on a terminal.
